Some info on my megadose infusions of vitamin c and breast cancer

-please note I’m not a doctor and I’m not giving health advice, just telling what I’m doing.
-I had to obtain doctor’s permission and have a GLUCOSE-6-PHOSPHATE DEHYDROGENASE, QN test to make sure I had the enzymes to process high dose vitamin c
-some types of cancer cells do have the enzyme catalase, and they respond less to megadose vitamin c
-forgive my struggling for words. I have brain fog and also a Robitussin hangover

Thanks for listening and following my journey ❤️

Look at these awesome wraps Rudy @overkillstrength made me!  Thank you Rudy - I love them!

I want to take a moment to thank Rudy, who has sponsored me over the years, through my single-ply and multi-ply endeavors.  We had lost touch after I took a break from lifting a couple years ago.

I was concerned I wouldn’t be able to lift at all after my cancer had returned in July. Rudy made a point to reach out and text me a kind message, but my favorite part was this: 

“I know you've also had your struggles but I also know how mentally and physically strong you are and have always overcome and accomplished everything you set out to achieve. This character is what Overkill is all about and I love supporting people who do extraordinary things.

We are currently building the sponsorship crew back up and on that note, I'd like to officially offer you back your sponsorship you earned if you'd have us.”

It’s difficult to convey how much a showing of support like that helps someone who’s been told they have a very serious life-threatening disease.  I felt like I could do anything. A lot of these sponsorships out here are really empty and demanding and one-sided.  I love that I’m sponsored by a company who really cares and values me.  Rudy didn’t even know if I could lift again, but was willing to sponsor me and be in my corner through some of my darkest days. I wish all sponsors were that awesome. 

Cheers to you, Rudy. I can’t wait to show you your faith in me and what I can do wasn’t misplaced.

We just wrapped up Tony’s bday weekend - and his first cruise and first time out of the country. 

Yesterday was the coldest winter day in the Bahamas in years - lol. So instead of the beach, we shopped and ate yummy food. 

We had a great time, but I confirmed I’m still not a cruise person. I’d much rather just fly somewhere and explore. I got trapped in a hot elevator a few too many times with people who recently vomited😂.

Training dump because I realize I haven’t posted any training videos in a while.  My recovery takes about twice as a long, and I feel about half as strong, but still putting in work :)

I’m working with a physical therapist who specializes in oncology patients, and she has me starting light and only increasing 10% a week, so I’m also learning patience (again - haha)

I believe this is the happiest I’ve ever seen Taki. This was from our walk this evening. I can’t watch it without smiling. I hope it has the same effect on you. 

#doggingsohard
Hey guys - just me here doing lifty stuff. Nothing exciting. But I was in a terrible mood before this and now I feel fantastic. It’s like magic :)

New challenge - pigeon press ups. 

These were assigned by my physical therapist, and they are no joke!  I do 3x8 on each side.  We are trying to strengthen the end range of my hip external rotation.  The other two exercises on the third slide are challenging, too.

I also have dry needling once a week on my left side on the areas highlighted in the second slide. 

We are trying to correct the problem with my left SI/glute Med/QL that has been bothering me for about 8 years now. While I can’t lift heavy yet, it’s a good time to tackle the dysfunction. 

If you try any of these, I’d love to hear about it.  Man they make my glutes sore!

This week was eventful and filled with family.  My mom came to visit from Ohio, we had a family lunch at a German restaurant, my cousin threw a wonderful wedding, we had a family breakfast, we came together when we had a medical scare with my baby nephew (who is much better now), and finally, we went on a scavenger hunt around Daytona with my sister and her family. 

Sometimes I forget how lucky I am to have such a close family.  I’m grateful my mom is here and doing well, my cousin is happily married, my niece is kicking ass at nursing school, and that my nephew is healthy and safe. 🙏
We played our hearts out today 💕

Look who I finally got to see today!!! 7 months later we finally got to do a hike in the Ocala National Forest. Both of our schedules finally aligned 🙌. I love you Lex! Thank you for making the drive. 

I’ve been hiking about a zillion times, but never found a tick. Today I found not one but THREE ticks on me 😩. Longest 1.5 hour drive home of my life! Could not wait to jump in the shower. I kept swearing I could feel things crawling on me 😑.

Taki got his first influencer job!

This Zoop stuff is awesome! We got bath wipes, which they say is better than an actual bath bc it leaves the sebum intact and deposits microscopic particles that help fight odor for 6 days. They are natural and can even be used on his teeth and all his sensitive parts.

We also got enzymatic odor and stain fighting spray (for our couch and the bedroom carpet, which he still occasionally pees on 😡), 

And we got this pet odor reed diffuser, which smells like citrus, and is nice and strong. 

I thought he would fight me on giving him the wet wipe bath, but he just laid there calmly. Much less stressful than our usual routine, which is having Tony throw him in the shower with me, I wash him as quickly as possible, then he takes about 3 hours to dry - even with help from a blow dryer!

We love all 3 products and want to try the rest of the things they offer ( please send more - lol). But seriously, I want to try the candle, the dry shampoo, and the itch relieving spray.  Will be watching for other stuff they develop- great brand!

My sweet nephew came by to hang out. He had to try on my all my medals and Tony’s Arnold belt. He’s a little athlete. I’m sure his collection is gonna blow ours away someday. Can’t wait to cheer him on ❤️
Our poor little angel is recovering from being fixed today.  Tony is out shopping for an inflatable collar. I had no idea how traumatic this would be for him. There has to be a better way.

Growing up, I was blessed to have 3 other cousins born within 3 months of each other.  My cousin Brian also lived with my family for most of our childhoods, so we were all extra close.  This made for many fun, happy  childhood memories to make up for a sometimes otherwise cruel life.  We stuck together through school, always keeping our little circle of lifelong friends.  As we grew up, we could spend months without contact, but always pick up right where we left off.  We had this unspoken connection, no matter where our lives took us. To say this was a gift is a massive understatement.

Last night, our little circle gathered around Brian and held his hand as he took his last breath. Then we met at the beach and shared funny happy memories and toasted to all his best qualities that will live on through us and our children.

Brian always felt he was never good enough, but the truth is, I never stopped admiring his sweet soul, kind heart, quirky sense of humor, humility, gentle manner, work ethic, loyalty, and ability to survive the most difficult life I've witnessed.  He wasn't successful in the material sense, but he made up for it in purity of heart.  He didn't allow the countless obstacles and adversity to change who he was at his core.  I hope when it's my time I'll be able to say the same.

Brian wasn't one to brag or show off, or take up much space.  He quietly survived.  That's part of why I felt compelled to post about him and give him some recognition he would've never expected or asked for. 

Brian, I'm proud of the man you were in all the ways that truly matter.  Thank you for all the love you put out into this world.  I am sorry you were dealt such a tough hand.  You deserved so much more.  I wish you would've let us help you more.  I wish I would've tried harder…told you more…done more.  You've been struggling since the day you were born.  I hope you finally find your peace.  You will be missed beyond words.

Dallas is my godson, and at 7 years old, is the strongest person I know.  He was born with gastroschisis and has spent much of the past few years in excruciating abdominal pain. Despite countless hospital stays and debilitating pain, he remains sweet, kind, helpful, and genuine. 

Watching his parents champion for him and fight for the right medical care has been inspiring, although frustrating. This truly is a family of superheroes. While dealing with all this, they went above and beyond and threw ME the most amazing fundraiser for my breast cancer back in October!

Dallas has his 8th surgery coming up. We hope this is the one that fixes what all of the others did not. We all know how expensive surgeries are, so a group of Jessica’s friends are getting together to try to help. 

There will be a Venmo set up soon, or if you find it in your heart to donate directly, you can send it to his mom Jessica Gibson @rushexperience.

Local businesses: if you'd like to support by making a donation or donating baskets/items/gift cards, I’ll happy to pick them up.

Mark your calendars for June 17th.  Please share & invite all you know so that we can show Dallas and his family that they're not in this alone. 

#DOITFORDALLAS

Last night was another amazing experience making happy memories with awesome people at the @olddominionmusic concert in Jacksonville.

We laughed, cried, sang, acted ridiculous, and had the best time!  I made new friends and spent quality time with some of my best forever friends. I wore a cowboy hat for the first time, traded shoes with someone I just met, took a dance lesson from a stranger (my friends knew him), had a last-minute dance party in Cindy’s apartment (happy bday Cindy!), and rode the 2 hours home in Kristina’s Jeep at 1 am. I felt ALIVE! It’s hard to believe I was getting chemo just a couple hours prior. Life is crazy.

I included a sped-up version of me trying to learn to dance. No idea what I was doing, but it was fun! 

Thank you a million, Jessica and Kristina 💕

#aboutlastnight #spendlifeliving #howdidigetsolucky

Natural hot springs - wish I could start every day like this 😍

Day 1! Also included some shots of the hike that almost ended our relationship 😂. It said moderate, but it was anything but.  Tony will never trust me for another hike - lmao 😂. Also volcanic mud mask, massage, and later will be a night jungle tour. This place was made for me 🌋🙏

Day 2 - wanted to share some of the animal friends we’ve made. We were so lucky to see a 6-month-old sloth moving through the trees up close!  We also saw a few poison frogs and a bullet ant, but didn’t get pics.

Sorry I fell behind posting my travel diary. Day 4 we drove from La Fortuna to Manuel Antonio. The drive was crazy! So many winding mountain roads. One video was from some sort of street promo with a dj trying to get people to buy panties at a store - lol.  The drink and snack selections were on point! Then we arrived at Costa Verde and were treated to a beautiful room with an awesome view 😍

I’m so grateful I was able to get a full 7-night trip with air, rental car, hotels, and breakfasts for $750 per person!

These are some pics and vids from my bday - we rented ATVs and rode through the palm farms and up the mountain to swim in a waterfall.  I yelled my head off and had the best time. It brought me back to my childhood. I loved letting loose and getting muddy with some of my bestest 🥰

I’m sure no one noticed, but I had removed my social media accounts while I focused on planning my cousin’s funeral and going through a real estate investment mentorship.  I’m back, and here are some sweet moments I experienced while away. 

The funeral was beautiful. My little 3-year-old nephew picked up the mic and started singing Hallelujah by himself! It was a wonderful time reconnecting with family. I’m especially proud of how my sister, brother, and I pulled together to plan, execute, and speak.

I rescued a baby dove.  He was a nestling Taki found in our yard. He was on the ground when a storm started, so I took him in, fed him, and kept him warm. We built him a makeshift nest and his mama and dad came back and fed him until he was strong enough to fly away! 

Taki ate someone’s weed they dropped on the beach and got very sick. The emergency vet took care of him and he’s all better now ($650 later 🤬). 

Taki survived his first 4th of July. He hated the fireworks, but was okay once we sound insulated his crate.
One inspiring one and a few that made me giggle

In these you can see my banged up knee from my car accident, but I kinda like it. The super talented Greg at @goodeggproductions shot these. It was a fun shoot, and no, I’m not on a trampoline. Just jumping up in the air. Not as easy as it looks! Which one is your favorite? #supergirl #superman #supermanpunch #photooftheday

I want to thank Tiffany and Rob for inviting us out on Rob’s bday deep sea fishing adventure today.  We had a great time! Happy bday Rob!!

I think we caught 24 fish. I caught (and released) an Atlantic shark (my high school mascot), a king fish, a trigger fish, a mahi, and like 6 vermillion Snapper. Eli caught that big 33? pound kingfish and Tony caught that big snapper we had to throw back. We brought the king fish to Grills at the port, and they blackened half and grilled half. It was SO DELICIOUS! Great day, but I am beat. 😴
Had my first hair date with Mama. It was about time!  Thanks @alisondoeshair_ for taking such good care of us 🩷

Tony’s first kayaking, first time at the springs, and first time seeing a manatee in the wild. If you notice, the kayak is struggling in the back 😂. Tony was complaining he was hungry, his hip hurt, and his foot was asleep 10 minutes into the trip.  I swear we almost tipped a few times, but we made it - with no collisions. It’s a miracle! Thanks for arranging it, Kim and Greg! Now NAP 😴

I want to thank Dr. Ortiz at @behealthychiropractic for taking such good care of me. This penguin suit felt especially good on my wrists and shoulders.  He combined that with the traction table and a neck traction roll. I love the ability to save time addressing multiple things at once. 

When I came to him a few weeks ago, scar tissue around my rib cage was making me struggle to breathe.  After 2 weeks of him working on me, that issue is completely resolved! 🎉

The FirsTrust family company picnic was at Discovery Cove this year. I’m lucky to have been included since I’m retired. I wish I had pics of us swimming with sharks and stingrays, or looking at monkeys and otters in the lazy river, but I was too busy being in the moment.  I loved having Kristen, Tony, and Atlas there.  To be surrounded by so many good people I love dearly… what a gift!

This was my first time benching in a very long time! It felt really good, but I had to practice restraint. I finally got my fascia around my rib cage to relax, thanks to help from @behealthychiropractic, so I don’t want to trigger more spasming.  Also, have to be mindful of the weakened bones in my lower spine, due to spaces left by what used to be tumors.  Considering all that, this felt phenomenal and like a good start 🙏

Their friendship is one of the best things about my life. I can’t think of a better way to celebrate. Thank you all!  On to the next chapter. I’m more excited about the future than I have ever been in my life.  The best is yet to come! 🙏💖

I AM A WALKING MIRACLE!

I just left the oncologist and finally convinced him to show me videos of all the tumors on my PET scans from back in October 2022  and again in June of this year. I began treatment in October 2022, and by December, all of my tumor markers showed the cancer was gone. When I see these side-by-side, I’m overcome with excitement and a feeling of victory.  I feel like I won the biggest war of my life.  I’m so grateful to have had the resources, support, and the mental fortitude to get here. I will remain on an AI inhibitor and get my tumor markers tested every couple of months, but for now, I can breathe a sigh of relief. 

The body is so amazing- it blows my mind.

Thank you to everyone who supported me through this, and continue to do so.  I couldn’t have done it without you! Especially Tony, who kept me laughing and supported me the best I’ve ever seen. 💗

I want to thank my medical team, who have been nothing short of amazing! 

Integrative Oncologist: Dr. Daniel Thomas at https://www.healthyandstrong.com/
Oncologist: Dr. William Grow at Florida Cancer Specialists
Integrative Physician: Dr. Jason Schottel at Anti-Aging and Regenerative Specialists

I get messages daily from people who are battling this monster or have loved ones facing it. I want to let everyone know that I’m happy to help however I can.  I’m just a message away. 

#breastcancerawareness  #breastcancer #breastcancerawarenessmonth

Taki likes to get all the dogs riled up at the dog park, then hide under me 😅. 

His fur was looking much nicer from the groomer’s, but last night around 11pm he decided to find some shit and roll around in it.  So Tony and I took turns washing him repeatedly in the shower then bathtub until the smell dissipated. 

I’m totally not complaining. These are the things we think back on and laugh. Even when he’s being a pain in the ass, it enriches our lives.

When I was originally diagnosed, my holistic onco told me to get a dog.  He said my chances of survival would be increased exponentially.  What an amazing doctor 😌. I have so much to thank him for.

Photo cred: @sirbenchalot1k 💗

This is late coming, but last weekend I got to celebrate the engagement of two of my best friends. I couldn’t be happier for Lex and Jake as they plan the happiest of futures together.  Lex and I go wayyy back to bodybuilding days, and I never would’ve imagined we would be engaged at the same time.  What an awesome gift - so much to celebrate!

Another highlight of last weekend (it’s been a whirlwind since Mexico!): my sister, cousin and I volunteered to set up a teacher’s lounge at a local elementary school, in an effort to give back to the people who educate our local kids.  Chrissy came up with the idea and we all came together to make it happen. 

We have a couple of finishing touches, then we will post before and after photos of the space.

This was such a cool project and brought us much joy, laughter, and fulfillment.  I’m grateful I have awesome, talented women in my family that are committed to stuff like this, and look forward to more projects together.

We had so much fun (God, I’m sore) doing an acro beach yoga day for Chrissy’s bday.  It brought me back to my old cheerleading days, where I was always better at being a base than a flyer 😂) @dynamicallyalignedyogi (Soraya) was an amazing instructor! She has a private studio in South Daytona with a yoga wall that is life-changing.  Check her out! www.dynamicalignmentyoga.com

Mary and I usually are terrible at getting pics together, so I’m super happy we got to capture this moment. 

This woman has been my best friend since we were 9 years old.  She has lived in New York the last 20-something years, and decided to move back to Florida after hearing about my diagnosis, so now we get to make all the memories!  I cannot think of a more touching gesture. If I talk about it, my voice cracks.  I’m honored beyond words 🙏💙. Thank you Mary 🥲

Last weekend, we attended our second @nolongerfatherless  gala.  It’s so awesome to watch this organization grow every year and make such a huge impact on the community. Please check them out if you’d like contribute or volunteer to be a mentor to boys in our area who don’t have a father.

Thank you for the invite, @chrissysellshomes! 
We had a great time supporting a wonderful cause and simultaneously celebrating Chrissy’s bday.

We all went skating last night for Chrissy’s bday (which is actually tomorrow if anyone wants to buy her a drink). We had more fun than expected.  Two people mentioned they were excited to go because they couldn’t wait to see Tony on skates 😅. 

Tony and Jake competed in a 16-and-older race. One of them came in second and one came in last. You guess which was which - lol. 

Thanks to everyone who took  and sent these pics! I’ve definitely been slacking in that department.
I like the short girl one the best 😅
I promise to make the most of every day I have left - to live life to the fullest and not waste this second chance at living my best life, on my terms.
